	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Aed. pl. , Dated to 83, with a query, in MRR 2.63, 65, note 4. See now Crawford, RRC 1.367, no. 351, 86 B.C. See below on M. Fannius (15).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4115> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4115" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Grueber, CRRBM 1.314f.; CIL 12.2, p. 756, no. 272." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4114> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4114" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "4 The absence of coins naming these Aediles from hoards buried about 86 suggests a terminus post quem, while the aedileship of Pomponius in 82 appears to provide a terminus ante quem. If the emblems on their coins refer to distributions of grain under Cinna they should be dated before 84. Sydenham (Ixii) dates them ca. 85." .
